result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer L. Downey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling (Waushara Co. Case 14CF174), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling (Waushara Co. Case 14CF174), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

miscConds.notes: Court orders restitution to be paid in increments of no less than $100 per month commencing January 1, 2016.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. The defendant is to have NO CONTACT with R Bar and Grill and/or Waupaca Country Club.

Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program.

records.addlTxt: 11:28 am case called. Defendant Jennifer L. Downey in court with attorney Chelsie A. Thuecks.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Consolidation of Waupaca County Case 14CF354. Agreement stated on the record by DA Blader. Attorney Thuecks agrees and defendant agrees. Court address preliminary hearing in Waushara County case-Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing and finds probable cause a felony has been committed within the courts jurisdiction. Court addresses consolidation and questions defendant. Defendant requests matter to be consolidated within Waushara County's matter. Information filed. Attorney Thuecks confirms receipt and waives formal reading. Defendant wishes to enter pleas.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Counts 1 & 2.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 3, 4, 5, & 6. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to-EACH COUNT: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 4 years. CONDITIONS: CT 1 only: 6 months WCJ, with Huber-No Good Time Credit. No Credit for time served. To begin no later than May 25, 2015. CONDITIONS on BOTH COUNTS: AODA and follow through,   maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No Contact with R Bar and Grill and/or Waupaca Country Club, Restitution in the amount of $2,101.97 to be paid in increments of no less than $100.00 per month commencing January 1, 2016. Costs to include Attorney Thuecks' fees- to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Terms of agent. Defendant to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD program.  Appeal Rights Given.
